
<div class="page-header">
  <h1>Bandwidth Usage</h1>
</div>

<div class="row">
  <div class="span4">
    <h2><%= @host.ip_address %></h2>
    <p>This is the IP address of the host in question.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="span12">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="span6">
        <h3>&#11015; Download</h3>
        <h4><%= number_to_human_size(@host.inbound)%></h4>
        <% if @host.inbound_restricted%>
          <p>
          <span class="label warning">Warning</span>
          This host's download speed is restricted.
          </p>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      <div class="span6">
        <h3>&#11014; Upload</h3>
        <h4><%= number_to_human_size(@host.outbound)%></h4>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <p>
      The above information is the amount of bandwidth consumed by that
      host during the peak hours of 1PM to 1AM. If the amount of data downloaded
      exceeds 1.5 GB, the host's download speed will be restricted to 512kbps.
      This limit is lifted once the amount used within the past 24 hours is less
      than 1.5 GB.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

